                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="rubrication">
                           <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                        </seg>
                        <desc>The word God is not rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works</desc>
                        <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#90v #91r" facs="092">folss. 90v, 91r, </locus> (Ps. 129); <locus target="#97v" facs="099">97v, </locus> (Ps. 150); <locus target="#104v" facs="106">104v, </locus> (ninth Biblical Canticle); <locus target="#104v #105r" facs="106">104v, 105r</locus> (tenth Biblical Canticle).</desc>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#iv(erso)" facs="002">Fol. iv(erso)</locus>
                        <desc> crude drawing of a figure</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2">
                        <locus target="#76r" facs="077">Fol. 76r</locus>
                        <desc> crude drawing of a talismanic symbol</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3">
                        <locus target="#120v" facs="122"> f. 120v, top</locus>
                        <desc>picture of a priest with prayer stick and sistrum with caption <q>“Zion;”</q> Underneath him is a person carrying the ark surrounded by two figures with arms upstretched and holding something over the ark.
                        To the left is an image of <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1066DavidHarp">David Playing the Harp</ref>, with the caption, <q>“As David the prophet prayed, I will pray to you, God, my creator”</q>
                        (an excerpt from God Reigns)</desc>
                        </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4">
                      <locus target="#120v" facs="122"> f. 120v, bottom center</locus>
                      <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref> with the two archangels on either side.  To the lower left is an <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1012Equestrian">Equestrian Saint</ref>, presumably Saint George</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5">
                        <locus target="#127v" facs="129">Fol. 127v</locus>
                        <desc> crude drawing of a figure</desc>
                     </decoNote>

                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d6">
                    	Decorative designs:
                      <locus target="#6v #120v" facs="008 122">folss. 6v, 120v, </locus> (haräg);
                      <locus target="#7r #20v #48v" facs="008 022 050">7r, 20v, 48v, </locus> (line of black dots);
                      <locus target="#13v #20v #29v #36r #67r #86r #93v #98r #118r #121r #122r #125v" facs="015 022 031 037 068 087 095 099 119 122 123 127">13v, 20v, 29v, 36r, 67r, 86r, 93v, 98r, 118r, 121r, 122r, 125v</locus> (multiple full stops between lines of alternating red and black dots).
                    </decoNote>
